div.p:
—On the Middle East, he stressed Israeli agressiveness and our responsibility for
                    it, given our “great influence” on Israel; and the familiar charge that we wish
                    to emplace military forces in a region on the USSR’s southern borders;

—If I were suggesting the need for more frequent exchanges, he said, the Soviets
                    support it, and are ready to talk on any issue except the Geneva
                    negotiations;
